{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"object"},{"type":"text","text":" is floating, sink it.  Otherwise, do nothing."}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ObjectRef","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ObjectRef\/ObjectProtocol-Implementations"]]},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"takeRef","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ObjectRef","preciseIdentifier":"s:10GLibObject0B3RefV","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ObjectRef"},{"text":"!","kind":"text"}],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"In other words, this function will convert a floating reference (if","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"present) into a full reference."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Typically you want to use ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_ref_sink()"},{"type":"text","text":" in order to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"automatically do the correct thing with respect to floating or","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"non-floating references, but there is one specific scenario where","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"this function is helpful."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The situation where this function is helpful is when creating an API"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"that allows the user to provide a callback function that returns a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"GObject. We certainly want to allow the user the flexibility to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"return a non-floating reference from this callback (for the case"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"where the object that is being returned already exists)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"At the same time, the API style of some popular GObject-based"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"libraries (such as Gtk) make it likely that for newly-created GObject","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"instances, the user can be saved some typing if they are allowed to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"return a floating reference."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Using this function on the return value of the user’s callback allows"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the user to do whichever is more convenient for them. The caller will"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"always receives exactly one full reference to the value: either the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"one that was returned in the first place, or a floating reference"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"that has been converted to a full reference.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This function has an odd interaction when combined with"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_ref_sink()"},{"text":" running at the same time in another thread on","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the same "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Object","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" instance. If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_ref_sink()"},{"type":"text","text":" runs first then"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the result will be that the floating reference is converted to a hard"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"reference. If "},{"code":"g_object_take_ref()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" runs first then the result will be","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that the floating reference is converted to a hard reference and an"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"additional reference on top of that one is added. It is best to avoid"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"this situation.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"metadata":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"takeRef","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:10GLibObject0B3RefV","text":"ObjectRef","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"!"}],"externalID":"s:10GLibObject0B8ProtocolPAAE7takeRefAA0bE0VSgyF::SYNTHESIZED::s:10GLibObject0B3RefV","title":"takeRef()","symbolKind":"method","role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"GLibObject"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Method","extendedModule":"GLibObject"},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ObjectRef\/takeRef()","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glibobject\/objectref\/takeref()"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"references":{"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject","url":"\/documentation\/glibobject","abstract":[],"role":"collection","kind":"symbol","title":"GLibObject","type":"topic"},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/ObjectRef":{"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ObjectRef","abstract":[{"text":"The base object type.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"ObjectRef","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/objectref","title":"ObjectRef","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ObjectRef","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol"},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/ObjectRef/ObjectProtocol-Implementations":{"type":"topic","kind":"article","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ObjectRef\/ObjectProtocol-Implementations","url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/objectref\/objectprotocol-implementations","title":"ObjectProtocol Implementations","role":"collectionGroup"},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/Object":{"url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/object","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Object","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Object","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","title":"Object","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Object","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The base object type."}],"role":"symbol"},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/ObjectRef/takeRef()":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"takeRef"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:10GLibObject0B3RefV","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"ObjectRef"},{"kind":"text","text":"!"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/objectref\/takeref()","title":"takeRef()","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ObjectRef\/takeRef()","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"object"},{"text":" is floating, sink it.  Otherwise, do nothing.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic"}}}